author: GamingBolt
description:
The twisted and messed up world of Death Stranding is brimming with bizarre yet utterly fascinating bits and pieces of lore, and in the lead up to Death Stranding 2: On the Beach's launch, we are continuing to take a deeper look at it. 

And there are few things in Death Stranding's world that are quite as fascinating as the concepts of Extinction Entities and BTs.
title: What Are BTs and Extinction Entities? - Death Stranding Lore - Before You Play Death Stranding 2

author: GamingBolt
description:
MindsEye is the debut sci-fi action-adventure from Build a Rocket Boy, a studio comprising Rockstar alumni with game producer – and once of Rockstar himself – Leslie Benzies at the helm. Coming on June 10th, MindsEye is the gripping, thematically heavy story of Jacob Diaz, an amnesiac soldier searching for clues amongst the technocratic streets of fictional US city Redrock as to the origin of his mysterious neural implant. 

With a deep, evolving storyline, awesome set pieces, highly polished cinematography, and dynamic gameplay, the comparisons to Grand Theft Auto – apt, given the team’s track record – don’t appear to be doing the game justice. This is very much a more tightly focused, narratively curated experience more so than the types of stories Rockstar tells. This video dissects fifteen things you need to know before you buy MindsEye.
title: MindsEye - 15 Things To Know Before You Buy This Ex-Rockstar Dev's Game
